  "prompt": "When friendship gets complicated what we should do?",
  "response": "When friendship becomes complicated, here are some helpful steps:\n\n1. Communicate openly\n- Have an honest conversation\n- Express your feelings clearly\n- Listen to their perspective\n\n2. Assess the situation\n- Understand what's causing complications\n- Identify specific issues\n- Reflect on the relationship's value\n\n3. Set healthy boundaries\n- Be clear about your expectations\n- Respect each other's limits\n- Maintain mutual respect\n\n4. Practice empathy\n- Try to understand their point of view\n- Put yourself in their shoes\n- Show compassion\n\n5. Give space if needed\n- Sometimes temporary distance helps\n- Allow time for reflection\n- Avoid unnecessary conflicts\n\n6. Consider professional mediation\n- If issues are deeply rooted\n- Seek counseling or neutral third-party advice\n- Get objective perspective\n\n7. Know when to let go\n- If the friendship becomes toxic\n- If there's consistent disrespect\n- If it negatively impacts your mental health\n\n8. Practice self-care\n- Prioritize your emotional well-being\n- Don't compromise your values\n- Maintain a positive mindset\n\n9. Learn and grow\n- Treat complications as learning opportunities\n- Understand relationship dynamics\n- Improve communication skills\n\nRemember, healthy friendships require mutual effort, understanding, and respect.",
